Princess Charlene of Monaco and her husband Prince Albert celebrated Monaco's National Day with a rare balcony kiss.

In an echo of the Duke and Duchess of Cambridge's famous balcony kiss following the 2011 royal wedding, the pair smiled lovingly before puckering up.

The couple, who are expecting twin babies next month, were joined at the Palais Princier de Monaco by the rest of the royal family, including Albert's sisters Stephanie and Caroline. 

