But it was pregnant Charlene, 36, who was centre of attention, thanks in part to her elegant cream coat and delicate pearl earrings.

Joining her on the balcony was the younger generation of royals, among them Pierre Casiraghi, his his brother Andrea and his son Sacha, as well as Princess Alexandra of Hanover.

The balcony appearance came as Monaco celebrated its 158th national day, which is takes place on the anniversary of Prince Rainier III's and Prince Albert II's coronations in 1949 and 2005.

Last night, locals enjoyed a spectacular firework display over the harbour before a mass in the Cathedral this morning.

